ABOUT ME

I was born in New Orleans, Louisiana. I moved shortly after to Texas due to hurricane Katrina. As I grew up I had an interest in wanting to understand how "things" work. Not too long into highschool I decided I wanted to become an engineer. I chose Computer Engineering as my degree path, as it gives me both a taste of hardware and software development. I enjoy software development as it gives me a chance to create anything to my imagination. Thinking out of the box and creating a solution to a problem is one of my favorite things to do, and software engineering allows me to accomplish that in many ways.
